><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
Disregarding parallax, -- but the reckoning is
with the 'eighth sphere,' <i>ad quam tota terra comparata
obtinet locum puncti</i>. St Thomas had some inkling of
the magnitude of the heavens. But what he calls <i>tota
terra</i> in this relation is a vaster quantity, the orbit 
of the earth.

